author: Nicola Agius
title: James Jordan evicted from Celebrity Big Brother house after brutal face-to-face nominations
text:
Get celebs     
James Jordan has been eliminated from Celebrity Big Brother. 
His shock departure from the show makes him the fourth housemate to lose their place in the competition. 
Although he was undoubtedly hoping to stay a little longer on the show, the former Strictly pro insisted he wasn't disappointed to be out. 
"It's okay, I'm going to my wife," he told the remaining housemates as said his goodbyes. James Jordan has been eliminated from Celebrity Big Brother (Photo: Channel 5) 
During his exit chat with presenter Emma Willis, James opened up about his departure. 
"Of course I am gutted to go but at the same time, I do get to see my wife so it's win win for me," he said with a huge smile on his face. 
Showing her support for her husband, Ola Jordan was sitting in the audience to greet James. 
Late arrivals Kim Woodburn, Chloe Ferry and Jessica Cunningham were safe from tonight's live eviction. 
However, they were each allowed to put two housemates forward to face the public vote. 
The trio will be up for eviction on Friday. 
*Celebrity Big Brother returns to Channel 5 on Wednesday at 9pm Like us on Facebook
